    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1843452863" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1843452863" />
    <a title="Matthew" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16254355-matthew"><img alt="Matthew" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1464987365p2/16254355.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1843452863?book_show_action=true">Jun 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matthew" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matthew" href="/user/show/16254355-matthew">Matthew</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140449266" href="/book/show/7126.The_Count_of_Monte_Cristo">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=classic">classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=at-home-reading">at-home-reading</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=revenge">revenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=2017">2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=completist-book-club">completist-book-club</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1843452863" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6047869831573661174">Over 1200 pages of suffering and revenge! <br/><br/>I enjoyed it. I did not like it quite as much as some of the other big classics I have read, but it was very good. The two things that brought it down a bit for me were:<br/><br/>- It felt a bit more drawn out than it needed to be. At a couple of points I was ready for Dumas to get to the point.<br/>- Some of the plot was very convoluted. While this did lend itself well to the Count&apos;s intricate plotting, I would occasionally get to a chapter and say, &quot;Wait, what!?&quot; A f</span>
  <span id="freeText6047869831573661174" style="display:none">Over 1200 pages of suffering and revenge! <br /><br />I enjoyed it. I did not like it quite as much as some of the other big classics I have read, but it was very good. The two things that brought it down a bit for me were:<br /><br />- It felt a bit more drawn out than it needed to be. At a couple of points I was ready for Dumas to get to the point.<br />- Some of the plot was very convoluted. While this did lend itself well to the Count's intricate plotting, I would occasionally get to a chapter and say, "Wait, what!?" A few times I tried to reorient myself with chapter summaries online, but stopped after it became difficult to avoid spoilers. <br /><br />With all the negative out of the way, I will say that is was definitely a great book. At times it was riveting. At others it was clever. At pretty much all times it was dark and seemingly hopeless. The unabridged is great because it has everything as Dumas wanted it, but it does require quite a bit of commitment.<br /><br />Final judgement: A must for those who want to read all the classics, but probably a bit much for the causal reader. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6047869831573661174" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1843452863">
